HeaderHSpiceCSDF - Class in be.kuleuven.micas.signalStorage.formats.spice
A helper class to read the header of a hspice ASCII CSDF file and construct a corresponding SimulationOutputHeader startOfData indicates the value of the first data-point, so little time is lost by splitting the reading procedure in two parts To output this file format in hspice, add these lines to the spice netlist: .OPTION CSDF Output is then dumped in netlistName.tr0 for transient netlistName.sw0 for dc sweep

HeaderPsfAscii - Class in be.kuleuven.micas.signalStorage.formats.psfAscii
A helper class to read the header of a HSPICE Ascii file and construct a corresponding SimulationOutputHeader startOfData indicates the value of the first data-point, so little time is lost by splitting the reading procedure in two parts To output this file format in spectre, add these lines to the spice netlist: option1 options rawfmt = psfascii ("option1" is the name of the simulation and can be anything you like)
